### Why we clear CACHE in DAX Studios?
When we execute a query, part of query, like the storage engine query is cached, is kept in memory already computed. And this is useful because the next time the engine needs same data,
it needs not to scan the whole database.
If we are doing analysis clearing the cache is important. If we do not clear cache we might not get accurate results. 
It ensures your query timings reflect actual runtime.

