### IMPORT vs DIRECT QUERY
Import Mode
Best For: Most users, small-to-medium datasets, high interactivity, complex modeling.
Pros: Fastest query performance (in-memory), full Power Query/DAX, no source dependency.
Cons: Data is a snapshot (needs refresh), size limits (Premium helps), potential large file sizes. 
DirectQuery Mode
Best For: Very large datasets, near real-time data, when you can't import.
Pros: No size limits, always fresh data, data stays in the source.
Cons: Slower performance (queries source live), limited transformations/DAX, source dependency. 


